Another property of LPG in its liquid form is its ability to greatly expand when heated. Therefore, NFPA 58, 1998 Edition sets the maximum filling capacity of large tanks in Table 4- 4.2.2(b) to avoid over filling.

Kiros procedures apply and follows the rules and regulations set forth in NFPA 58, 1998 Edition.

Personnel Training

Kiros shall coordinate and maintain records of personnel training. All personnel who work with or around hazardous substances will attend a hazard communication training class. Additionally, such personnel shall attend an annual refresher course. The class will provide at a minimum information about:

	Chemicals in the workplace and their hazards;
	How to minimize exposure;
	Procedures to follow if exposed;
	Location of SDS;
	How to read SDS, placards, and other warning labels;
	Proper handling of substances;
	How to recognize and report releases and other hazards;
	Proper evacuation procedures and emergency contact protocol; and
	Location and proper use of PPE
As required under 40 CFR 68.54, training requirements for new operators at Kiros include training on operating procedures and must cover health and safety hazards, emergency operations, and safe work practices applicable to the employee normal job or function
